"{\"uid\": \"kpcw.org-wasatch-county-2024-01-16-wasatch-county-wants-to-finish-bypass-before-2034-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Plans for a bypass road to circumvent Heber City's Main Street have been in the works for decades.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 98, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 38, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999948491904, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heber City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, with the Olympics potentially returning to Utah in 2034, leaders are seeking an expedited timeline for that road.\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999955459771, \"rank\": 4.42877388283706e-09, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wasatch County manager Dustin Grabau said he's been involved in local planning efforts around the future Olympics.\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 219, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999942232307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wasatch County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 249, \"end\": 255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"score\": 0.9999999952229928, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grabau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Largely we have discussed the need for identifying projects that the community views as important that might also have a connection with the Olympics,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We hope that the bypass could be in place by then, because I think transportation from Utah County and through Wasatch County is going to be an important aspect of it.\\\"\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_County,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999310609861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Utah County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_County,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_County,_Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999942232307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wasatch County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasatch_County,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the Deer Valley expansion could be a key location for a future Olympics and facilitating access would be critical.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The future boundaries of what land Heber City could annex are also under consideration in the bypass discussion.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999948491904, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heber City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The anticipation has always been that the bypass would represent kind of the northwest boundary of Heber City,\\\" Grabau said.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999948491904, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heber City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"score\": 0.9999999952229928, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grabau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, with proposed routes on the table, Heber's leaders are expected to discuss the city's boundaries at a meeting Saturday.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reginald_Heber\", \"score\": 0.5424493530660425, \"rank\": 0.8303759679279934, \"text\": \"Heber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reginald_Heber\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reginald_Heber\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grabau said Heber City does not anticipate annexing all the North Fields even if the bypass cuts through that land.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"score\": 0.9999999952229928, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grabau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amadeus_William_Grabau\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999948491904, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heber City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At this point, the Utah Department of Transportation has identified five possible bypass routes to pull traffic away from downtown Heber.\", \"from\": 1275, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Three possibilities begin just south of Heber City and reconnect to U.S. 40 north of downtown.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999999948491904, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heber City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heber_City,_Utah\"}, {\"begin\": 1481, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._Route_40_in_Utah\", \"score\": 0.999999987066417, \"rank\": 1.281368796452661e-08, \"text\": \"U.S. 40\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._Route_40_in_Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U.S._Route_40_in_Utah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two others would connect much farther north, passing through the agricultural North Fields.\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"UDOT is expected to announce its preferred route by March.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Department_of_Transportation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UDOT\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Department_of_Transportation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah_Department_of_Transportation\"}]}]}"